cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about training MaxPooling Convolutional Networks for image segmentation, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for training these networks, which involves optimizing the weights of the network using backpropagation. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm in terms of speed, which could make it relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
